node.text:
Just do it! Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen.
Hebrews 11:1. 

In tough times, when life doesn’t make sense, when your prayers aren’t answered, when it’s taking longer than you thought it would, my question is, do you have your anchor of hope down? When  you’re anchored to hope, it’s as though you’re tied to it. Do you have that hope, that expectancy that your dreams are coming to pass, that you’re going to break that addiction, that your family is going to be restored? Or have you pulled up your anchor, and now you’ve drifted into doubt, mediocrity, and not expecting anything good? Are you saying, “This problem is never going to work out” rather than “I know the answer is already on the way”?

Put your anchor back down. “Faith is the substance of things hoped for.” You can’t have faith if you don’t first have hope. You have to believe that what God put in your heart will come to pass, that you will accomplish your dreams, that you’ll meet the right people, and that you’ll live healthy and whole! #realtalkkim

node.text: I decree that you begin to  experience restful sleep like never before. In Jesus name, I break the power of restlessness, sleeplessness, insomnia, tensions, and physical distress that would rob you of a good nights rest. I cast out every nightmare and night terror and I say it cannot operate ever again around you or your home! I speak peace to your mind and body during the night hours. I say that every muscle, bone, sale, organ and hormone must align itself correctly so you are able to rest. I speak peace to the environment around you and say that you operate in God’s promise that he gives his beloved sleep. I speak Sweet sleep upon you and may your nights be restful, comfortable, relaxing, and calm. I say that your nights of sleep shall be the best and most rejuvenating yet! Amen

My PRAISE BREAK today coming from you from our 12:00 service here in Sacramento. Straight 🔥🔥 I have made a commitment to my @mylimitlesschurch to be in my pulpit most Sundays. I only miss about five Sundays a year, so if I miss it’s gotta be a good reason. Today, was one of my reasons and I had the honor of ministering for my friend  @pastorsamuelrodriguez at @newseasonsacramento in and it felt like I was home. Powerful Sunday! @annjones “mimi” filled in for me and she crushed it! Thank you Lord for trusting me. Thank you Lord for all of it. Everything I’ve had to go through to get to this moment in my life. Every mistake I made, every storm I went through. Every terrible life lesson I had to learn from. Every lie I outlived, All of it. It was worth it ALL to be right here right now! The oil hits different when you have days like today! My heart is GRATEFUL! I love you Jesus! See you next Sunday @mylimitlesschurch l’ll be HOME and it’s my 49th BIRTHDAY 🥳 come celebrate with MEEEEEEEEE. Love you all. How was your church today. What did your pastor preach? Shout them out!

node.text: Stop waiting for a YES from people before you say to God! God qualifies you! What stumps us up in life is waiting on people to recognize who we are. All you need is to Surrender your life to God and watch Him show out! Your best is yet to come! He values you! He calls you! He chooses you! He’s waiting on you! Let’s go!!
